title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1983-04-26
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street-> Minglewood Blues, They Love Each Other, Me and My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, Maybe You Know How I Feel, West LA Fadeaway, My Brother Esau, It Must Have Been the Roses, Let It Grow

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Women Are Smarter-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Nobody's Fault But Mine-> Morning Dew-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: U.S. Blues

Days between 2017

Not sure if this is the recording you want... Great sounding matrix, though a bit heavy basswise. Fantastic show! The only issue is the tracks cut off at the end too early with disconcerting frequency. Gotta listen to some others (there are LOTS of them after all) and see if any are better.
